Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.push

Interface CloudPushListener

  • public interface CloudPushListener

    A CloudPushListener is added to a CloudPush service. The CloudPushListener can be used to process registrations, messages and errors a client received.

    Since:
    1.4

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • registered

        void registered​(java.lang.String instanceId,
                java.lang.String token)

        Will be called after a client has registered itself for push notifications. The passed token identifies the client and can be used to send push notifications using the platform specific push services.

        Parameters:
        instanceId - a stable identifier that uniquely identifies the app installation.
        token - the token a client received after a successful registration.

      • tokenChanged

        void tokenChanged​(java.lang.String token)

        Will be called when the current registration token has changed.

      • instanceIdChanged

        void instanceIdChanged​(java.lang.String instanceId)

        The event is fired asynchronously when the CloudPush.resetInstanceId() method is invoked.

      • messageReceived

        void messageReceived()

        Will be called when a client has received a push notification. The forwarded message can be obtained by calling CloudPush.getMessage().
